 land, rather than those affected by land acquisitions. Fairbairn's work sheds ethnographic light on the actors and relationships—from Iowa to Manhattan to São Paulo—that have helped to turn land into an attractive financial asset class.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAgriculturexCapital investments. 0aAgriculturexEconomic aspects. 0aAgriculturexFinance. 0aFarmsxForeign ownership. 0aFinancialization. 4aAgriculture. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aGeography-Physical & Cultural. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geography.2bisacsh  aBrazil, financializaion, political ecology, agricultural geography, rural sociology, land policy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishz978311070475408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501750106?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501750106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501750106/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070475-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  a